Synchronous Approach:

sync code is executed in squence.
Each statements waits for the previous statement to finish before executing.

Asynchronous Approach:

async code doesn't have to wait for your program.
Altough your program can continue to run.
Do this to keep the site application to be responsive.
Helps in reducing the waiting time for the user.

to write async code in JS/Node, you can use:
    1. Callback
    2. Promises
    3. Async/Await